	<div class="slide3">

		<p>It can also be used for 'Abbreviations', such as 'Timmy Jr'</p>

		<p>If you are writing a sentence, in most cases, you can use the period from the abbreviation to end the sentence itself</p>

		<p>Example: My name is James Haroldson, Jr<span>.</span></p>

	</div>
	<div class="slide4">

		<p>Relating to the last topic, they can be used in personal titles, such as 'Mr.', 'Mrs.' etc.</p>

		<p>Most people don't know this, but if the title starts and ends with its coresponding word, it doesn't need a period.

